FBIS3-17703 "drsov060_b_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Yeltsin Confers With Stepashin on Security Issues LD2903112694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1048 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903112694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Moscow, 29 Mar (ITAR-TASS) -- President of Russia Boris Yeltsin today held a meeting in the Kremlin with Sergey Stepashin, the chairman of the Russian Federation Counterintelligence Service, the Russian president's press secretary reported. During the conversation, which lasted for 40 minutes, they discussed general issues of Russian security and also current business of the counterintelligence service. The Russian president stressed the need for a strong and professional special service defending the interests of Russia and the democratic state. He pointed out the need to enhance the efficiency of the counterintelligence service. Sergey Stepashin briefed the president on the progress and initial findings of the investigation into the appearance and publication of the so-called "Version No 1", about preparations for a coup d'etat, and those involved in this falsification. The Federal Counterintelligence Service and Procuracy have set up a joint group to complete the investigation. According to existing information, the Rssian Federation Procuracy has launched criminal proceedings in connection with the case for defamation (Article 130 of the Russian Federation Criminal Code).
